## Context

Second `MetadataResolver` implementation, against the Crossref REST API. Same
interface as the OpenAlex resolver (ticket 0003). Used as a fallback when
OpenAlex returns no candidate above the threshold.

- User-Agent includes `mailto:` from `config.contact.mailto` (Crossref polite pool).
- Honors `config.http.*` timeouts, retries, backoff, rate limit.
- Search strategy: if input has DOI → `GET /works/<doi>`; else
  `GET /works?query.title=<title>&query.author=<first-author>&rows=5`,
  filtered by year ± 1.
- Same scoring (`rapidfuzz` title + author overlap) and same
  `config.matching.*` thresholds as OpenAlex.

## Actions

1. `src/maiba/resolvers/crossref.py` — `CrossrefResolver` implementing
   `MetadataResolver`.
2. Map Crossref's response shape (`message.title[0]`, `message.author[*].family`,
   `message.container-title[0]`, `message.published-print.date-parts`, etc.)
   to `Item`.
3. `tests/test_resolve_crossref.py` — see Test. `respx` mocks all HTTP.

## Test (TDD red step)

Replay the captured Crossref responses from
`tests/fixtures/responses/crossref/` (created in ticket 0006). Every test
case is grounded in real server output.

```python
# tests/test_resolve_crossref.py
import json
import respx
from httpx import Response
from pathlib import Path
from maiba.config import load_config
from maiba.model import Item
from maiba.resolvers.crossref import CrossrefResolver

CFG = load_config("config/maiba.yaml")
FIXTURES = Path("tests/fixtures/responses/crossref")

def _replay(slug: str) -> dict:
    return json.loads((FIXTURES / f"{slug}.json").read_text())

@respx.mock
def test_resolve_by_doi_hit():
    respx.get(
        "https://api.crossref.org/works/10.1016/j.egypro.2009.02.302"
    ).mock(return_value=Response(200, json=_replay("ashworth-2009-doi")))

    resolver = CrossrefResolver(CFG)
    item = Item(TY="JOUR", TI="Engaging the public on CCS",
                AU=["Ashworth, P.", "et al."], PY=2009,
                DO="10.1016/j.egypro.2009.02.302")
    result = resolver.resolve(item)
    assert result is not None
    assert result.source == "crossref"
    # Real Crossref response: container-title may be a list, dates may be
    # published-print or published-online. The mapping must handle both.
    assert "Ashworth" in " ".join(result.candidate.AU)

@respx.mock
def test_resolve_returns_none_when_search_too_noisy():
    # Crossref returned 3 unrelated items for the LeMonde Sleipner search.
    # Below the matching threshold → resolver returns None.
    respx.get(url__startswith="https://api.crossref.org/works?").mock(
        return_value=Response(200, json=_replay("lemonde-sleipner-2008-search"))
    )
    resolver = CrossrefResolver(CFG)
    item = Item(TY="NEWS",
                TI="Sleipner, pionnière de l'enfouissement du gaz carbonique",
                AU=["Le Monde"], PY=2008)
    assert resolver.resolve(item) is None
```

## Exit criteria

- `make test` green; no real HTTP in tests.
- Endpoint and headers configurable via `Config`.
- Same `MetadataResolver` shape as ticket 0003 — interchangeable in the pipeline.
